summary: In this context, chlorobenzene and dichlorobis(ethylenediamine)rhodium(III) are both mentioned as part of a study involving the biodegradation of organic compounds in aquifers. However, there is no direct interaction or relationship discussed between the two compounds. Chlorobenzene is listed among other organic compounds analyzed for isotopic composition, while dichlorobis(ethylenediamine)rhodium(III) is not specifically addressed in relation to chlorobenzene or the biodegradation process.
